      <div xml:id="NA63-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu (EV: talaivaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉāka) alar accattāl tōḻi ciṟaippuṟamākac ceṟippaṟivuṟīiyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how, out of the fear of gossip, the confidante informed [him] of [her] being confined while [he] was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA63">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uravukkaṭa luḻanta peruvalaip paratavar</l>
<l>            mikumī ṉuṇakkiya putumaṇa lāṅkaṭ</l>
<l>            kalleṉ cērip pulavaṟ puṉṉai</l>
<l>            viḻavunāṟu viḷaṅkiṇar virintuṭaṉ kamaḻu</l>
<l>            maḻuṅka lūrō vaṟaṉiṉ ṟataṉā </l>
<l>            laṟaṉi laṉṉai yaruṅkaṭip paṭuppap</l>
<l>            pacalai yāki viḷivatu kollō</l>
<l>            puḷḷuṟa vocinta pūmayaṅ kaḷḷaṟ</l>
<l>            kaḻiccura nivakku miruḷciṟai yivuḷi</l>
<l>            tiraitaru puṇariyiṟ kaḻūu </l>
<l>            malitiraic cērppaṉō ṭamaintanan toṭarpē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>As for [our] noisy village, where the Puṉṉai tree,</l>
<l rend="indent2">so that the noisy quarter doesn't smell of fish,</l>
<l rend="indent">emits fragrance as soon as it spreads [its] shining clusters,</l>
<l rend="indent3">smelling of festival,</l>
<l rend="indent2">there by the new sand where much fish is put to dry</l>
<l rend="indent2">by the fishermen with big nets that had borne the strong sea</l>
<l rend="indent3">– it is devoid of duty.</l>
<l rend="indent4">Therefore,</l>
<l rend="indent3">having turned into pallor,</l>
<l rend="indent3">while [our] virtueless mother ordains strict protection,</l>
<l rend="indent4">will it perish,</l>
<l>our attachment settled with the man of the coast of growing waves,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the horses wash in the wave-bringing ocean,</l>
<l rend="indent">yoked in darkness coming up through the backwater desert,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in perturbed mire with flowers broken open as the bees come in?</l>
        </lg>
         </div>
